  <h3>When to use a primary button</h3>
  <p>Use a primary button for the main call to action on a page, for example to help users start an application or save their progress.</p>
  <p>Use only 1 primary button on a page. Having more than 1 reduces their impact and makes it harder for users to know what to do next.</p>
  <p><a href="#when-to-use-buttons">More about when to use and not use buttons.</a></p>


  <h2 id="secondary-button">Secondary button</h2>
  <p>There are 2 versions of the secondary button.</p>
  <p>By default, the secondary button is transparent and has no colour. Use it on the page background colour (<code>nhsuk-colour("grey-5")</code>).</p>

  {{ designExample({
    group: "components",
    item: "buttons",
    type: "secondary"
  }) }}
  <p>You can make the button white when you use it on darker backgrounds. Use the <code>.nhsuk-button--secondary-solid</code> class to maintain colour contrast.</p>

  {{ designExample({
