    <strong class="nhsuk-tag nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-2">WCAG 2.2</strong>
    <p>Do not decrease the height or target area of buttons. This is to make sure users can easily interact with them. It complies with <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/target-size-minimum.html">WCAG 2.2 success criterion 2.5.8 Target Size (W3C)</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Disabled buttons</h3>
  <p>Disabled buttons have poor contrast and can confuse some users. Only use them if user research shows it makes things easier for users to understand.</p>

  <h4>Colour contrast</h4>
  <p>All our buttons pass AA guidelines for colour contrast. The disabled versions of the buttons do not meet accessibility colour contrast ratios. If your team has discovered a user need for disabled buttons, use them carefully and test them with users with access needs.</p>

  <h3 id="grouping-buttons">Grouping buttons</h3>
  <p>Use a button group when 2 or more buttons are placed together. The buttons will display side by side on wider screens. On smaller screens, such as on mobile, they'll appear above each other.</p>

